---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
const updated = 'April 27, 2026';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy policy for kameir.com, operated by Decentralized Publishing LLC."
  noIndex={false}
>
  <article class="privacy">
    <div class="container">

      <header class="privacy__header">
        <p class="label">Legal</p>
        <h1 class="privacy__title">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="privacy__meta">Last updated: {updated}</p>
      </header>

      <div class="privacy__body prose">

        <p>
          This website, <strong>kameir.com</strong>, is operated by
          <strong>Decentralized Publishing LLC</strong> ("we," "us," or "our"),
          a limited liability company headquartered in the United States.
          This policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, and
          your rights with respect to it.
        </p>

        <h2>1. Information we collect</h2>

        <h3>Analytics</h3>
        <p>
          We use <a href="https://plausible.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Plausible Analytics</a>,
          a privacy-first analytics service. Plausible does not use cookies,
          does not fingerprint your browser, and does not collect or store
          any personally identifiable information. The aggregate traffic data
          it records — page views, referrers, country of origin, device type —
          cannot be used to identify you individually. No consent banner is
          required because no personal data is processed.
        </p>

        <h3>Contact form</h3>
        <p>
          The contact form on this site is powered by
          <a href="https://formspree.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Formspree</a>.
          When you submit the form, the information you enter — your name,
          email address, and message — is transmitted to Formspree's servers
          and forwarded to us by email. Formspree processes this data under
          its own
          <a href="https://formspree.io/legal/privacy-policy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">privacy policy</a>.
          We retain your message for as long as necessary to respond to your
          inquiry and for legitimate business record-keeping.
        </p>

        <h3>Server logs</h3>
        <p>
          Our hosting provider (ChemiCloud) may collect standard web server
          logs, including IP addresses, browser user-agent strings, and
          request timestamps. These logs are used solely for security,
          performance, and abuse prevention purposes and are not shared
          with third parties except as required by law.
        </p>

        <h2>2. Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          This site does not set any first-party cookies. Plausible Analytics
          operates without cookies. No advertising networks or tracking
          pixels are present on this site.
        </p>

        <h2>3. How we use your information</h2>
        <p>
          Information you submit via the contact form is used solely to
          respond to your inquiry. We do not sell, rent, or share your
          personal information with third parties for marketing purposes.
          We do not build advertising profiles from site visitors.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Legal basis for processing (EEA and UK visitors)</h2>
        <p>
          If you are located in the European Economic Area or the United
          Kingdom, we process any personal data you provide through the
          contact form on the basis of your consent (Article 6(1)(a) GDPR)
          and, where applicable, our legitimate interest in responding to
          business inquiries (Article 6(1)(f) GDPR). You may withdraw
          consent at any time by contacting us.
        </p>

        <h2>5. California residents (CCPA / CPRA)</h2>
        <p>
          California residents have the right to know what personal
          information we collect, to request deletion of that information,
          and to opt out of any sale of their information. We do not sell
          personal information. To exercise your rights, contact us at the
          address below. We will respond within 45 days as required by law.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Data retention</h2>
        <p>
          Contact form submissions are retained for as long as the
          associated business relationship or inquiry is active, and
          thereafter only as long as required for legitimate business
          or legal purposes. Server logs are typically retained for
          30 days and then deleted automatically.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Data security</h2>
        <p>
          All traffic to and from this site is encrypted via HTTPS (TLS).
          We take reasonable technical measures to protect information
          transmitted to us, but no method of transmission over the
          internet is completely secure.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Third-party links</h2>
        <p>
          This site may contain links to third-party websites. We are
          not responsible for the privacy practices or content of those
          sites. We encourage you to review their privacy policies before
          providing any personal information.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Children's privacy</h2>
        <p>
          This site is not directed at children under the age of 13. We
          do not knowingly collect personal information from children.
          If you believe a child has submitted personal information to us,
          please contact us and we will delete it promptly.
        </p>

        <h2>10. Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this policy from time to time. The date at the
          top of this page reflects the most recent revision. Continued
          use of the site after a change constitutes acceptance of the
          updated policy.
        </p>

        <h2>11. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions or requests regarding this privacy policy should be
          directed to:
        </p>
        <address class="privacy__address">
          Decentralized Publishing LLC<br />
          Newport Beach, California, United States<br />
          <a href="/contact">Contact form</a>
        </address>

      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
/* ── Header ───────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.privacy__header {
  padding-top: 4rem;
  padding-bottom: var(--space-l);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  margin-bottom: var(--space-l);
}

.privacy__title {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
  font-weight: 700;
  line-height: 1.1;
  letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  margin-top: 0.75rem;
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
}

.privacy__meta {
  font-family: var(--font-ui);
  font-size: 0.85rem;
  color: var(--text-muted);
  margin: 0;
}

/* ── Body ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.privacy__body {
  max-width: 680px;
  margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
}

.privacy__body h2 {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-size: 1.15rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--text);
  margin-top: 2.5rem;
  margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
}

.privacy__body h3 {
  font-family: var(--font-ui);
  font-size: 0.8rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--text-muted);
  margin-top: 1.75rem;
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
}

.privacy__body p,
.privacy__body address {
  font-size: 0.975rem;
  line-height: 1.85;
  color: var(--text-muted);
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}

.privacy__body a {
  color: var(--text);
  text-decoration: underline;
  text-underline-offset: 2px;
}

.privacy__body a:hover {
  color: var(--accent);
}

/* ── Address ──────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.privacy__address {
  font-style: normal;
  background: var(--bg-subtle);
  border-left: 3px solid var(--border);
  padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
  border-radius: 0 2px 2px 0;
  line-height: 2;
}

/* ── Responsive ───────────────────────────────────────────── */
@media (max-width: 640px) {
  .privacy__header {
    padding-top: 2.5rem;
  }
}
</style>
